The paper deals with face recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors use an information theoretic framework to estimate the capacity of a given face representation, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning-based approaches, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve processing large amounts of data, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations and vulnerabilities of face recognition systems, which could fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR).
